            <div class="col-md-12">
            
                <p class="sub-title pad-bt15"><b><i>“Our cultural strength has always been derived from our diversity of understanding and experience.” - Yo-Yo Ma (United Nations Messenger of Peace)
                </i></b></p>
                <p class="sub-title pad-bt15"> Appreciation for cultural diversity is essential for our co-existence. Learning to acknowledge that all cultural differences are valid, respecting each other’s differences and valuing what different cultures bring to the table are basic lessons we learn to incorporate in our Cultural Diversity classes by Mr. Charles and Ms Sahana, which are nothing short of exciting and engaging. </p>
            

                <p class="sub-title pad-bt15">In the last two weeks, we have discussed the significance of sports in promoting cultural diversity and bringing the world together. This gripping session was conducted by our seniors who left us with a lot of knowledge and sowing in us an interest in understanding the interrelation between culture and sports. Ranging from discussing various prominent sports figures and their impact in the field of sports to understanding the history of sports, the session had it all. 
                </p>
                <p class="sub-title pad-bt15">We had yet another captivating session where we discussed how culture and food are intertwined and understood more about gastronomy. We discussed the various ways the UNESCO recognizes gastronomic traditions as intangible culture and ensures that they are celebrated. We were exposed to different food etiquettes around the world and how incumbent it is to know and respect them. Lastly, we deliberated over the importance of advertisement in the food industry and how it popularized the same. </p>

